<p>Thomas Cruise Mapother IV (born July 3, 1962) is an American actor and producer. One of the world's highest-paid
    actors, he has received various accolades, including an Honorary Palme d'Or and three Golden Globe Awards, in
    addition to nominations for three Academy Awards. His films have grossed over $4 billion in North America and over
    $11.1 billion worldwide, making him one of the highest-grossing box office stars of all time. Cruise began acting in
    the early 1980s and made his breakthrough with leading roles in the comedy film Risky Business (1983) and action
    film Top Gun (1986)</p>
